ethersrv is an implementation of EtherSRV for Linux and FreeBSD. It allows a
Linux or FreeBSD computer to share its drive over Ethernet with multiple DOS
clients running EtherDFS.

This is version 20180203 from http://etherdfs.sourceforge.net/ plus FreeBSD port
and some other patches by me.

FreeBSD example:

  $ su
  [...]
  $ mdconfig -f /home/michael/floppy.img -u 0
  $ mount -t msdosfs /dev/md0 /mnt
  # ./ethersrv -f em0 /mnt
  Listening on 'em0' [...]
  Drive C: mapped to /mnt
  # ls -lo /mnt
  [...]
  -r-xr-xr-x  1 michael  wheel  hidden,rdonly,system      7 Jun  6 10:41 test.txt

Thanks and Greetings to Mateusz Viste.

Enjoy,
Michael
